{"MISGET":[{"def":"To get wrongfully.","pos":""}],"MISGIVE":[{"def":"To give or grant amiss.","pos":""},{"def":"Specifically: To give doubt and apprehension to, instead of confidence and courage; to impart fear to; to make irresolute; -- usually said of the mind or heart, and followed by the objective personal pronoun.","pos":""}],"MISGIVING":[{"def":"Evil premonition; doubt; distrust.","pos":""}],"MISGOTTEN":[{"def":"Unjustly gotten.","pos":""}],"MISGOVERN":[{"def":"To govern ill; as, to misgovern a country.","pos":""}],"MISGOVERNANCE":[{"def":"Misgovernment; misconduct; misbehavior.","pos":""}],"MISGOVERNED":[{"def":"Ill governed, as a people; ill directed.","pos":""}],"MISGOVERNMENT":[{"def":"Bad government; want of government.","pos":""}],"MISGRAFT":[{"def":"To graft wrongly.","pos":""}],"MISGROUND":[{"def":"To found erroneously.","pos":""}],"MISGROWTH":[{"def":"Bad growth; an unnatural or abnormal growth.","pos":""}],"MISGUESS":[{"def":"To guess wrongly.","pos":""}],"MISGUIDE":[{"def":"To guide wrongly; to lead astray; as, to misguide the understanding.","pos":""}]}